/KATEFILAT GESHEM / THE PRAYER FOR RAIN/XX/PR

Our God, our ancientsò God:/PR

/PR

With raindrops of Ancient light, illuminate the earth./PR

With raindrops of Blessing divine, please bless the earth./PR

With raindrops of Gleeful rejoicing, give joy to the earth./PR

With raindrops of Divine exultation, enrich the earth./PR

With raindrops of Heavenly splendor, give glory to the earth./PR

With raindrops of Wise assembly, let the earth be gathered./PR

With raindrops of Song and melody, make music through the

earth./PR

With raindrops of Healing life, enable earth to live./PR

With raindrops of Timeless good, give goodness to the earth./PR

With raindrops of Your saving help, redeem the earth./PR

With raindrops of Caring nurturance, nourish the earth./PR

/PR

For you are /SCT/XXHE /XXF/XXOUNT OF /XXL/XXIFE/XX, our God, abundant in your
saving acts, who makes the wind to blow and rain to fall./PR

/PR

For blessing, not for curse./PR

For living, not for death./PR

For plenty, not for dearth./PR

/ITThe ark is closed. Continue the Festival /MDAmidah/XX on page 334./PR

